Senate Republican Leader Robert Doleof Kansas said Alan Greenspan would be a good replacement forPaul Volcker as Federal Reserve Chairman.    "While Paul Volcker's retirement is a real loss, thiscountry is very fortunate to have a man of Alan Greenspan'scaliber to take his place," Dole said in a statement.    "Alan's knowledge of the economy, coupled with hisexperience at the top levels of government, means that theleadership of the Federal Reserve Board will be in good hands.Alan, literally, has some big shoes to fill. But I haven't anydoubts he's more than equal to the task," Dole said. Reuter&#3;